<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-29-0138 </DOCNO><TEXT>The author describes flaws in the Reagan administration's cooperativefederalism policy, particularly where renewable energy projects are concerned.In Oregon, an Alternate Energy Development Commission has provided acomprehensive plan for renewable resource development. The programs developedas a result of this plan have saved $77 million annually in energy bills.However, federal restrictions are impeding the states ability to financeresidential solar and energy conservation projects.</TEXT></DOC>